[1]
Date: Mon 4 Apr 2005
From: Marianne Hopp <mjhopp12@yahoo.com>
Source: World Health Organization (WHO), CSR, Disease Outbreak News, Mon 4
Apr 2005 [edited]
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_04_04/en/>

Viet Nam: avian influenza situation - WHO update 14
-----------------------------------------------
As of 4 Apr 2005, the Ministry of Health in Viet Nam has confirmed 5
additional cases of human infection with the H5 subtype of avian influenza
virus (see previous report
<http://www.who.int/csr/don/2005_03_29b/en/>).
All 5 cases are in a family from the northern port city of Haiphong. The
cluster includes the 35-year-old father, the 33-year-old mother, and their
3 daughters, aged 13 years, 10 years, and 4 months. All cases in this
family were hospitalized on 22 Mar 2005 and remain under care.
Since mid-December 2004, Viet Nam has reported 33 cases of H5N1 avian
influenza. Of these cases, 15 have been fatal. The cumulative number of
confirmed human cases of avian influenza A/(H5N1) since 28 Jan 2004 can be
accessed at
<http://www.who.int/csr/disease/avian_influenza/country/cases_table_2005_04_
04/en/>.
